<li>Among these predicted targets under the direct control of RgrR , as many as 11 genes are included , including PgrR , LeuO , YagP , MarR , YpdA , XapR , YhgF , GadX and IdnR ( indicated in star in Table 1 ) , indicating that a number of genes must be regulated indirectly by PgrR .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23301696" target="_blank">23301696</a>]<br></li>
<li>aerobic to anaerobic anaerobic to aerobic ArgR CysB BirA DgsA MalT GadW MetJ NikR OxyR SoxR SoxS DcuR CueR FadR HcaR NtrC PhoB PurR SgrR TdcA TrpR ZraR ArcA CpxR CRP CusR FhlA Fis FNR Fur H-NS IHF IscR Lrp ModE NarL NrdR PdhR FlhDC GlcC EvgA GadX LeuO PspF RbsR steady states Figure 3 .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22870390" target="_blank">22870390</a>]<br></li>
<li>In this case , form II appeared to be prevalent , but the binding afﬁnity of the promoter was apparently lower than that of PgadA , as indicated by the fact that a substantial amount of the PgadB remained unbound in the presence of 10 pmol of MalE-GadX .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11976288" target="_blank">11976288</a>]<br></li>
<li>Thus , while complex I is stably retained up to saturating concentrations of MalE-GadX , complexes II and III appear to be mutually exclusive .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11976288" target="_blank">11976288</a>]<br></li>
<li>In fact , it is reasonable to imagine that at low concentrations of GadX ( 0 -- 25 nM ) , heterologous H-NS-GadX-DNA complexes , which are transcriptionally inactive , are formed .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15795232" target="_blank">15795232</a>]<br></li>
<li>For example , in steady-state cultures , as aerobiosis increased , the excretion of acidic fermentation end-products decreased [ 4 ] , and the acid responsive regulators EvgA and GadX exhibited correspondingly lower activities ( figure 3 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22870390" target="_blank">22870390</a>]<br></li>
<li>Chimeric MalE-GadX was found to activate the gad system in vivo , although to a much lesser extent than the wild-type GadX protein , as expressed from pQEgadX and pBsX .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11976288" target="_blank">11976288</a>]<br></li>
<li>The induction of mdtE by indole is independent of the EvgSA two-component signal transduction system that regulates the mdtE gene , but mediated by GadX .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15686558" target="_blank">15686558</a>]<br></li>
<li>The global regulator cyclic AMP receptor protein ( CRP ) administers additional control over GadX production , tying it to the carbon energy state of the cell .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12940989" target="_blank">12940989</a>]<br></li>
<li>The higher concentration of cobalamin in cytoplasm will initiate riboswitch mechanism to repress the translation of BtuB receptor , which is in good accord with the repression of btuB transcription by the acid-induced GadX for bacteria to decrease the production of BtuB in response to this acidic stress .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21314918" target="_blank">21314918</a>]<br></li>
<li>Altogether , these data demonstrate that acetylation of lysine 154 of RcsB impairs its function , affecting flagella biosynthesis and B A flhDC FlhDC RcsB RcsA fliLMNOPQR fliE flgMN flgKL fliFGHIJK fliC 1 -3 -2 -1 0 2 3 4 flgAMN FlgM CobB flgBCDEFGHIJK RcsB RcsB AcK Acetyl-P motAB cheAW flhBAE Signal transduction Response to external stimulus fliDST FliA fliAZY Chemotaxis Locomotion Ciliary or flagellar motility Cell motility Cellular component organization or biogenesis Cellular component organization Response to chemical stimulus Cell projection organization Response to pH Metabolic process Cellular metabolic process Cellular response to stress Response to stress Response to abiotic stimulus Response to DNA damage stimulus Cellular catabolic process Catabolic process Small molecular metabolic process Carboxylic acid metabolic process Small molecule catabolic process Carboxylic acid catabolic process C GadX RcsB GadE GadX RcsB GadE RcsB GadE gadE mdtEF gadA gadX slp dctR gadBC cadBA GadW gadW hdeAB ydeP hdeD Figure 5 .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=25518064" target="_blank">25518064</a>]<br></li>
<li>The data also showed that each protein binds strongly to the 20 bp Gad box region , although GadX can weakly bind adjacent areas .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12940989" target="_blank">12940989</a>]<br></li>
<li>Since GadX control over gadE appeared to require the region upstream of 2360 bp , we tested whether GadX , purified as a maltose-binding fusion , could bind to this region .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17660422" target="_blank">17660422</a>]<br></li>
<li>This binding could inhibit GadX activity .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12446650" target="_blank">12446650</a>]<br></li>
<li>Discussion In this study , we performed a genome-wide search for a regulator of multidrug resistance in E. coli by random shotgun cloning and discovered GadX , which upregulates mdtEF , thereby increasing resistance to β-lactams , erythro-mycin , rhodamine 6G , and SDS .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18297445" target="_blank">18297445</a>]<br></li>
<li>Here , we report that the AraC-family regulator GadX increases multidrug resistance in E. coli through activation of the MdtEF efﬂux pump .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18297445" target="_blank">18297445</a>]<br></li>
