<li>Gene Gene product OD 4 NaCl OD 4 pH 5 ( Irp mutant ) b 5.80 3.96 3.48 9.16 4.46 2.07 2.79 1.38 8.68 32.38 16.44 10.28 11.26 6.61 2.52 3.68 3.48 13.06 2.33 2.22 2.22 1.65 1.28 1.27 1.08 0.99 1.14 Glutamate decarboxylase A , isozyme , PLP dependent 39.58 21.23 29.72 9.17 5.87 3.64 5.19 3.23 19.38 gadA gadB gadC hdeA hdeB hdeD slp yhiU gadE b3517 b1493 b1492 b3510 b3509 b3511 b3506 b3513 b3512 Glutamate decarboxylase , PLP dependent , isozyme beta Putative glutamate gamma-aminobutyric acid antiporter ( APC family ) Conserved protein with protein HNS-dependent expression Conserved hypothetical protein Putative membrane protein Outer membrane protein , induced after carbon starvation Multidrug-resistance protein ( lipoprotein ) Transcriptional regulator for gadABC operon , activates glutamate decarhboxylase-dependent acid resistance Transcriptional regulator for GadX ( regulatory protein ) , glutamic acid decarboxylase ( GadA , - B ) , and glutamate transport protein ( GadC ) Transcriptional regulator for glutamic acid decarboylase and transporter ( gadA , gadBC ) 12.39 gadW b3515 5.98 6.12 3.09 gadX b3516 9.39 3.14 7.45 6.09 a For explanations of data , see the footnotes to Table 1 .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15716429" target="_blank">15716429</a>]<br></li>
<li>The global regulator cyclic AMP receptor protein ( CRP ) administers additional control over GadX production , tying it to the carbon energy state of the cell .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12940989" target="_blank">12940989</a>]<br></li>
<li>The higher concentration of cobalamin in cytoplasm will initiate riboswitch mechanism to repress the translation of BtuB receptor , which is in good accord with the repression of btuB transcription by the acid-induced GadX for bacteria to decrease the production of BtuB in response to this acidic stress .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21314918" target="_blank">21314918</a>]<br></li>
<li>Interestingly , the genes coding for local regulators of the genes for individual amino acids are under the control of Lrp , including AdiY ( a regulator of Arg regulon ) , CysB ( a regulator of the Cys regulon ) , GadW ( a regulator of Glu reg ¬ Lrp Network Y J YhjI AdiY OLm r pR BluR YbaO YedW CadX CadW SdiA PhoP H-NS Cbl CysB TyrR TdcR DeoT TdcA CadX CadW DctR SdiA EnvR TdcA TdcA FabR StpA GadW LeuO GadE GadW GadX DtcR SlyA LeuO BglG StpA QseB Rob LrhA MatA NanR ~ 20 TFs FlhDC FliE LrhA FlhDC ~ 10 TFs FliZ MatA FlhDC QseCB Fig. 6 .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=2162465" target="_blank">2162465</a>]<br></li>
<li>The cAMP receptor protein ( CRP ) also plays a role in this RpoS-GadX pathway by tempering expression of RpoS during growth under conditions that result in high cAMP levels ( Ma et al. , 2003b ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19220752" target="_blank">19220752</a>]<br></li>
<li>The transcriptional regulator GadX also induces gadE expression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21193607" target="_blank">21193607</a>]<br></li>
<li>Indole signaling for mdtEF expression is independent of the EvgSA pathway but mediated by GadX , which is also an AraC / XylS regulator that cooperates with YdeO ( 5 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16885453" target="_blank">16885453</a>]<br></li>
<li>In order to characterize the RpoS-GadY ( Hfq ) - GadX signaling-pathway , we measured the growth phase-dependent changes in the expression of the rpoS , gadY , hfq , and gadX genes by means of the - galactosidase reporter assay .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16885437" target="_blank">16885437</a>]<br></li>
<li>Moreover , an involvement of GadX in the RpoS-inde-pendent , acid-responsive pathway of induction of the gad genes ( 7 ) is inferred by the evidence that stationary-phase expression of gadA and gadBC genes in the gadX mutant is more drastically reduced at acidic than at neutral pH. However , the observation that transcription of gadA and gadBC is only partially abrogated in the gadX mutant raises the possibility that additional positive regulators are also involved in the transcriptional tuning of the gad system , as found for other genes controlled by transcriptional regulators of the AraC/XylS family ( 22 , 25 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11976288" target="_blank">11976288</a>]<br></li>
<li>Based on evidence that GadX is involved in controlling this AR regulon and that the genes of interest are acid inducible , the following criteria for membership in the regulon were established : ( i ) expression is affected by mutation of gadX and ( ii ) induction occurs in acid conditions .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12730179" target="_blank">12730179</a>]<br></li>
<li>This would mean that the intracellular GadX level is sufﬁcient to activate transcription of the chromosomal copies of the gad structural genes , including gadC , resulting in increased expression of the GadC antiporter .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11976288" target="_blank">11976288</a>]<br></li>
<li>This suggests that overexpression of either GadX or GadE alone , in an FB8 genetic background , is not sufﬁcient to induce expression of genes involved in the bacterial response to low pH when cells are grown at neutral pH. Overexpression of gadX signiﬁcantly induced the expression of 48 genes of the H-NS regulon ( Table 3a ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=14702398" target="_blank">14702398</a>]<br></li>
<li>Chromosomal localization of genes involved in the low pH response Many genes identiﬁed by DNA array analysis ( Table 3 ) are regulated by both GadX and GadE .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=14702398" target="_blank">14702398</a>]<br></li>
<li>plays a key role in the de novo synthesis of pyrimidine nucleotides ( Bouvier et al. , 1984 ) , the gadAX operon encoding glutamate decarboxylase A and a global regulator GadX of the gad regulon ( Ma et al. , 2002 ; 2003 ) , the gadBC operon coding for glutamate decarboxylase B and glutamate-gamma aminobutyrate ( GABA ) antiporter ( Richard and Foster , 2003 ) , the ygiF-glnE operon for glutamine-synthesis from glutamate ( Van Heeswijk et al. , 1993 ) , and the gcl-hyi-glxR operon for degradation of allantoin ( Cusa et al. , 1999 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17919280" target="_blank">17919280</a>]<br></li>
<li>The latter circuit is also the most complex because apart from GadX and GadW , it also involves the global regulators H-NS and CRP , which act as transcriptional repressors , and RpoS , which positively affects gadA and gadBC transcription ( De Biase et al. , 1999 ; Castanie-Cornet and Foster , 2001 ; Hommais et al. , 2001 ; Tramonti et al. , 2002 ; Giangrossi et al. , 2005 ; Weber et al. , 2005 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18808381" target="_blank">18808381</a>]<br></li>
<li>Using genome-wide technologies such as transcriptome analysis ( Velculescu et al. , 1997 ) , GadX was identiﬁed as a regulator of the glutamate decarboxylase genes from the AraC family in E. coli ( Hommais et al. , 2001 ; Ma et al. , 2002 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=14702398" target="_blank">14702398</a>]<br></li>
<li>GadX has been previously demonstrated to be involved in the transcriptional activation of the glutamate decarboxylase system ( gadA/B , gadC ) as a direct activator of these genes , which were up-regulated by overexpression of gadX ( Hommais et al. , 2001 ; Ma et al. , 2002 ; Tramonti et al. , 2002 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=14702398" target="_blank">14702398</a>]<br></li>
<li>Discussion In this study , we performed a genome-wide search for a regulator of multidrug-resistance in E. coli by random shotgun cloning and discovered GadX , which upregulates mdtEF , thereby increasing resistance to β-lactams , erythro-mycin , rhodamine 6G , and SDS .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18297445" target="_blank">18297445</a>]<br></li>
<li>Then we investigated the susceptibility of the ΔacrB strain overexpressing gadX to various drugs , including common substrates of multidrug efﬂux pumps , and found that GadX stimulated E. coli resistance to oxacillin , cloxacillin , nafcillin , erythromycin , rhodamine 6G , and SDS ( Table 3 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18297445" target="_blank">18297445</a>]<br></li>
<li>J Infect Chemother ( 2008 ) 14:23 -- 29 DOI 10.1007 / s10156-007-0575-y © Japanese Society of Chemotherapy and The Japanese Association for Infectious Diseases 2008 ORIGINAL ARTICLE Kunihiko Nishino · Yasuko Senda · Akihito Yamaguchi The AraC-family regulator GadX enhances multidrug-resistance in Escherichia coli by activating expression of mdtEF multidrug efﬂux genes Received : August 24 , 2007 / Accepted : October 29 , 2007 Abstract Multidrug efﬂux pumps contribute to the resistance of Escherichia coli to many antibiotics and biocides .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18297445" target="_blank">18297445</a>]<br></li>
<li>Quantitative real-time polymerase chain reaction ( PCR ) showed that GadX activated the expression of mdtEF but none of the other drug efﬂux pumps in E. coli .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18297445" target="_blank">18297445</a>]<br></li>
