<li>In addition to these trans-acting proteins , the production of GadX is also controlled by gadY that is located between gadX and gadW in an opposite orientation to gadX [ 28,29 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21314918" target="_blank">21314918</a>]<br></li>
